sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64972
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: reid williams
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Simple composition of promoter, three reading frames, terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: creD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the last gene in the creD operon used in the TCA cycle. It is the alpha subunit of the succinyl-COA synthease. creC is the other subunit required for functionality.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Ritterson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The E Coli genome number from the K12 line.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: creD RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ribosomal binding site of the creD gene in the E Coli creD operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Ritterson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: creC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The third gene of the cre operon in E Coli. It is a protein kinase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Ritterson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: none- wild type sequence from genome.
